docs.abstract: The moderates who secured the Democratic House majority are feeling the heat from the new progressives who took seats in liberal bastions — and the constituents at home who oppose them.
docs.snippet: The moderates who secured the Democratic House majority are feeling the heat from the new progressives who took seats in liberal bastions — and the constituents at home who oppose them.
docs.lead_paragraph: NEPHI, Utah — In the suburbs of Salt Lake City, Representative Ben McAdams, a freshman, was grilled by constituents about the “socialism” and “anti-Semitism” that they saw coming out of the new Democratic House.

headline.main: In Conservative Districts, Democrats Have to Answer for Party’s Left Wing
headline.print_headline: The Moderates Take a Grilling Back at Home
